22/10/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A mass grave containing the bodies of about 60 victims of the communist regime has been found near the southeast town of Vlasotnice.
Srdjan Cvetkovic is secretary of the state commission working to find mass graves of people killed after 1944.
He said on Thursday (October 21st) that this is the second mass grave from the communist period uncovered this year.
The first one was near Boljevac.
(B92, Beta, Radio Free Europe - 21/10/10)
